        "description": "*Get Matt's favorite AI tools:* https://clickhubspot.com/jfd\n\nEpisode 101: Are AI social media agents replacing real creators on platforms like Meta? Matt Wolfe (https://x.com/mreflow) and Joe Fier (https://www.youtube.com/@joefier) dive deep into this week’s major AI releases and the evolving role of autonomous agents.\nThis episode explores cutting-edge updates from OpenAI, Anthropic, and Canva—including interactive visual explainers and Canva’s Magic Layers—and how these tools transform user experience and content creation. The hosts also unpack Meta’s acquisition of Maltbook, the viral social media network for AI agents, and discuss the broader implications for creators, businesses, and marketers. Plus, with clips from Sam Altman and Jensen Huang, the conversation turns to the future of intelligence as a commodity, the rise of agent-optimized marketing, and the changing value of intuition versus IQ. Robots, new prompt formulas, and the \"deader internet\" theory round out this lively, unpredictable episode.\n\nCheck out The Next Wave Podcast if you’re on the go and want to listen to the show: https://lnk.to/thenextwaveyt\n\n—\nShow Notes:\n00:00 — Intro: Visual AI Week\n01:00 — ChatGPT Visual Explainers (Pre-Built, ~70 Demos)\n05:00 — Testing ChatGPT: Compound Interest & Gas Laws\n07:00 — Claude Interactive Charts Drop — Generated on the Fly\n08:00 — Head to Head: Claude vs ChatGPT Visuals\n11:00 — Live Demo: Padres Schedule Calendar in Claude\n14:00 — The Prompt That Unlocks Claude's Visual Mode\n22:00 — Anthropic/Pentagon Interactive Timeline (This Gets Crazy)\n28:00 — Flow Charts, Abstraction Layers & Richard Feynman Mode\n38:00 — Canva Magic Layers: Break Any Image into Editable Layers\n41:00 — Live Demo: Thumbnail Redesign with Magic Layers\n45:00 — AI Infographic → Editable Canva Layers\n50:00 — Political Photo Shenanigans (Peak Matt & Joe Energy)\n57:00 — Sam Altman: AI as a Metered Utility\n01:00:00 — On-Prem AI = Going Off-Grid from Sam's Meter\n01:07:00 — Jensen Huang: Smart = EQ + Intuition, Not IQ\n01:14:00 — IQ Is a Commodity — What Actually Builds Wealth\n01:19:00 — Meta Acquires Molt Book (The AI Agent Social Network)\n01:26:00 — Matt's Theory: Meta Wants to Cut Creators Out\n01:30:00 — Agent Optimization: Marketing to Bots, Not Humans\n01:34:00 — Dead Internet Theory Gets Deader\n01:36:00 — Helix O2 Living Room Cleanup Robot Demo\n01:41:00 — Humanoid Robots vs Purpose-Built Robots Debate\n01:43:00 — Alexa Gets Sassy & OpenAI Pulls Back on Adult Mode\n01:46:00 — Matt's Rant: Is This Really \"For the Benefit of Humanity\"?\n\n—\nMentions:\nJoe Fier: https://www.youtube.com/@joefier\nManus: https://manus.im/\nClaude: https://claude.ai/\nGemini: https://gemini.google.com/app\nCursor: https://cursor.com/\nCanva: https://www.canva.com/\nMaltbook: https://maltbook.com/\n\nGet the guide to build your own Custom GPT: https://clickhubspot.com/tnw\n\n—\nCheck Out Matt’s Stuff:\n• Future Tools - https://futuretools.beehiiv.com/\n• Blog - https://www.mattwolfe.com/\n• YouTube- https://www.youtube.com/@mreflow\n\n—\nCheck Out Nathan's Stuff:\nNewsletter: https://news.lore.com/\nBlog - https://lore.com/\n\n\nThe Next Wave is a HubSpot Original Podcast // Brought to you by Hubspot Media // Production by Darren Clarke // Editing by Ezra Bakker Trupiano",
